page.title: 14Population and Expansion
page.content:
Wybunbury today is no longer a village of older citizens.An influx of younger people has meant that the average age of the population has been reduced.The arrival of the new inhabitants has also meant that the community is no longer as closely knit as it once was.Recent housing developments are in no small part responsible for this surge back to the country.
People in the upper wage bracket and self employed business men have also been moving into the area, living in renovated, modernised farm houses.
In general the population of Wybunbury can be defined as essentially middle-class.
